################################################

git-settings.sh: 
	A script to set useful global git settings (aliases, user-name and 
	user-email,...)

split-repo.sh:
	This program excludes a folder in an existing git-repository to 
	a new git-repository.

################################################
################################################

## git-settings.sh:

Usage:

 -h|--help
       print this helpmenu

 -l|--list
      list all existing global git settings

 -s|--set-alias <COMMAND ALIAS>
      set command as alias
      example: -s status st

 -c|--config
      set configuration for git:
      * alias
      * color
      * editor
      * mergeOption

      set following alias:
      ALIAS |  COMMAND:
      -----------------------------------------------------------------
      st    |  status
      ci    |  commit
      br    |  branch
      co    |  checkout
      df    |  diff
      he    |  help
      cl    |  clone
      nfm   |  merge --no-ff
      ffm   |  merge --ff-only
      dcw   |  diff --color-words
      tree  |  log --decorate --pretty=oneline --abbrev-commit --graph

################################################

## split-repo.sh:

Usage: split-repo ORIGIN-REPO NEW-REPO"

	Functionality:"
	START      |    END"
	----------------------------"
	XYZ/       |    XYZ/"
	   .git/   |        .git"
	   ABC/    |        XYZ1/"
	   XYZ1/   |        XYZ2/"
	   XYZ2/   |    ABC/"
	           |       .git/"
	
	INFO: The NEW-REPO must be a part of the ORIGIN-REPO"
